            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "۳۹۳. وَقَالَ (عليه ‏السلام): خُذْ مِنَ الدُّنيْا مَا أَتَاكَ، وَتَوَلَّ عَمَّا تَوَلَّى عَنْكَ، فَإِنْ أَنْتَ لَمْ تَفْعَلْ فَأَجْمِلْ فِي"
            }
          ]
        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/nahj-al-balagha:3:250:1",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/3/393/491",
        "text": [
          " الطَّلَبِ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
            "393. Amīr al-mu’minīn, peace be upon him, said: Take off the favours of the world whatever comes to you and keep away from what keeps away from you. If you cannot do so be moderate in your seeking."
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
